<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,946,1117]" pageId="8" pageNumber="555">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,563,946,972]" pageId="8" pageNumber="555">Report as epibiont on bryozoans:</emphasis>
This species was reported on bryozoans and algae from Strait of 
<collectingCountry box="[1339,1432,946,972]" name="Georgia" pageId="8" pageNumber="555">Georgia</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[151,235,982,1008]" name="Canada" pageId="8" pageNumber="555">Canada</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Wailes, G. H." box="[250,393,982,1008]" pageId="8" pageNumber="555" refId="ref8024" refString="Wailes, G. H. (1943) Canadian Pacific fauna. 1. Protozoa. 1 f. Ciliata. 1 g. Suctoria. University of Toronto Press, Toronro, 46 pp." type="book" year="1943">Wailes 1943</bibRefCitation>
; Mccazuley &amp; Hancock 1971).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="555" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,946,1117]" pageId="8" pageNumber="555">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,621,1018,1044]" pageId="8" pageNumber="555">Report as epibiont on other hosts:</emphasis>
The species is widely distributed, in particular, was found in Xiamen (Amoy), 
<collectingCountry box="[254,321,1054,1080]" name="China" pageId="8" pageNumber="555">China</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Wang, C. C. &amp; Nie, D. S." box="[335,542,1054,1080]" pageId="8" pageNumber="555" pagination="285 - 385" refId="ref7926" refString="Wang, C. C. &amp; Nie, D. S. (1932) A survey of the marine protozoa of Amoy, Nanking. Contributions from the Biological Laboratory of the Science Society of China, 8, Zoological Series 9, 285 - 385." type="book chapter" year="1932">Wang &amp; Nie 1932</bibRefCitation>
) on algae, also on the vertical walls of a tidal channel cut into mangrove peat in Twin Cays (
<collectingCountry box="[286,359,1090,1116]" name="Belize" pageId="8" pageNumber="555">Belize</collectingCountry>
Barrier Reef, the Caribbean Sea) (
<bibRefCitation author="Bauer-Nebelsick, M. &amp; Bardele, C. F. &amp; Ott, J. A." box="[747,1066,1090,1117]" pageId="8" pageNumber="555" pagination="18 - 30" refId="ref5004" refString="Bauer-Nebelsick, M., Bardele, C. F. &amp; Ott, J. A. (1996) Redescription of Zoothamnium niveum (Hemprich &amp; Ehrenberg, 1831) Ehrenberg, 1838 (Oligohymenophora, Peritrichida), a Ciliate with ectosymbiotic, chemoautotrophic bacteria. European Journal of Protistology, 32, 18 - 30. https: // doi. org / 10.1016 / S 0932 - 4739 (96) 80036 - 8" type="journal article" year="1996">
Bauer-Nebelsick 
<emphasis box="[943,992,1090,1116]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="555">et al</emphasis>
. 1996
